chunk_content: Do not count individuals who initiate treatment too late in the reporting period to be able to reach a minimum of 6 months by the time of reporting. How to review for This indicator makes use of program data as part of an ongoing cohort. The MAT register and/or data quality: patient-level data can be used to determine the number of people starting MAT in the defined period, as a cohort, and the number of those who are still in treatment at 6 months and who were on MAT for at least 6 months during the reporting period. Data should be reviewed regularly for the purposes of program management, to monitor progress towards achieving targets, and to identify and correct any data quality issues. How to calculate N/A. Data is reported only once annually at Q4.
